The state wants Changamwe MP Omar Mwinyi to face fresh charges.The office of the Director of Public Prosecutions wants Mwinyi to plead to new charges preferred by the office after the court declared the previous ones unconstitutional. State counsel Yamina Jami said she received instructions from DPP Keriako Tobiko to charge Mwinyi.Jami said the fresh charges were under a different section of the Constitution. On Monday, Mwinyi told the court ODM has already launched disciplinary action against him so it should wait for the party&rsquo;s verdict before charging him.Mwinyi was accused of causing chaos during ODM polls.